==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uplander
<hw>Up"land*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
dwelling in the upland; hence, a countryman; a rustic.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The upland sandpiper.</def>
<mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uplandish</ent>⟦br⟧
